---
source: crates/faultline-cli/src/main.rs
expression: help
---
Local-first regression localization for Git repos

Usage: faultline [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  reproduce        Extract a reproduction capsule from a completed run
  diff-runs        Compare two analysis runs side-by-side
  export-markdown  Export a Markdown dossier from a completed run
  completions      Generate shell completions for bash, zsh, fish, or powershell
  help             Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --repo <REPO>
          [default: .]

      --good <GOOD>
          

      --bad <BAD>
          

      --first-parent
          

      --cmd <CMD>
          

      --program <PROGRAM>
          

      --arg <ARGS>
          

      --kind <KIND>
          [default: custom]

      --timeout-seconds <TIMEOUT_SECONDS>
          [default: 300]

      --output-dir <OUTPUT_DIR>
          [default: faultline-report]

      --max-probes <MAX_PROBES>
          [default: 64]

      --resume
          Explicit resume from cached observations (default behavior)

      --force
          Discard cached observations and re-probe

      --fresh
          Delete entire run directory and start from scratch

      --no-render
          Skip HTML report generation

      --shell <SHELL>
          Shell to use for --cmd predicates (sh, cmd, powershell)

      --env <ENVS>
          Environment variable injection (KEY=VALUE), repeatable

      --retries <RETRIES>
          Number of probe retries for flake detection (0 = no retries)
          
          [default: 0]

      --stability-threshold <STABILITY_THRESHOLD>
          Minimum proportion of consistent results to classify as stable (0.0–1.0)
          
          [default: 1]

      --markdown
          Also write a Markdown dossier alongside HTML/JSON

  -h, --help
          Print help

  -V, --version
          Print version
